Nigeria’s president, Muhammadu Buhari has called on security agencies and communities under threat of bandits’ attacks and kidnappings to be more vigilant and alert in the light of the latest incidents in Enugu, Zamfara, Adamawa, Katsina and Kaduna States. The president who was reacting to recent reports of heightened acts of violence and kidnappings, according to his spokesperson, Garba Shehu, observed that, “in view of the unpredictability of the security situation, our security forces & the communities affected should be ever more alert because these murderous and remorseless criminals would take advantage of your complacency and strike again.”